`Locally.rightContinuous (hX : Locally (fun X ↦ ∀ ω, Function.RightContinuous (X · ω)) 𝓕 X P) : ∀ᵐ ω ∂P, Function.RightContinuous (X · ω)`

This is saying: given that the property "for all `ω`, `X · ω` is right-continuous" holds locally for the process `X`, then it holds almost surely.

This is a direct application of the definition of local property. If `p` is a local property, then `p` holds almost surely.

In Lean, we need to extract the fact that `∀ ω, X · ω` is right-continuous holds almost surely from the local property.

